            <p>Yuesisaurus is a genus of herbivorous dinosaurs in the family Ankylosaurus that lived at the end of the Cretaceous period about 75 millon years ago in what is now Liaoning Province in China.
                Juicysaurus was a relatively small and light ankylosaur, reaching a length of about 5 meters. 
                It had a long tail covered with spines and a long dorsal crest that could be used for defense against predators. 
                Juicysaurs were omnivorous animals, eating both plant and animal food.
